Bahrain Government To Address Housing Shortage, BNA Reports

-- B y   T a m a r a   W a l i d
-- 
2011-03-09T05:10:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/bahrain-government-to-address-housing-shortage-bna-reports.html
Bahrain will spend 2.5 billion
dinars ($6.63 billion) on building housing units to tackle a
shortage in the kingdom, the state-run  Bahrain News Agency  said
on Monday.  The Persian Gulf country plans to build 50,000 units over
the next five years, the Manama-based news agency reported,
citing Housing Minister Majeed al-Alawi.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Tamara Walid in Abu Dhabi at 
 twalid@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
